        <num>CCP 3287</num>
        <heading>3287.  Household goods</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3287.  Household goods
A succession representative may sell household goods at prices not less than the appraised value of such goods in the succession inventory or descriptive list by obtaining an order authorizing sales, from time to time, for such prices as the succession representative shall determine.  No advertisement shall be necessary, and the order authorizing such sales may be rendered upon the filing of the petition.  Household goods shall include furniture, furnishings, appliances, linen, and clothing.  If the succession representative desires to sell household goods for less than the appraised value, advertisement shall be required.</p>
        </content>
